# LeadFlow — Cursor Rules

## What this project is
A lead generation platform. Leads are ingested from external sources, validated,
scored, and surfaced to buyers. The pipeline is the product; the vertical
(mortgage, insurance, etc.) is configurable.

## Naming rules — enforce always
- Never use country names in type names, component names, file names, or copy.
  Wrong: CanadaLeadRow, canada-payload.ts, "Canadian mortgage leads"
  Right: LeadRow, mortgage-payload.ts, "mortgage leads"
- Vertical-specific logic lives in lib/processing/verticals/
- Types are market-agnostic. Market/country is a data field, not a type name.

## Domain model
source → raw_record → (processing) → lead → handoff

- raw_records: append-only. Never mutate payload. Processing state lives here.
- leads: promoted records only. A lead exists because it passed qualification.
- handoff: when a lead is sold/delivered to a buyer.
- Source attribution on a raw_record is set at ingest and is immutable.
- Qualification scores are always computed server-side, never client-side.

## Silent failure rules — the most important rules in this file
The processing pipeline has three failure modes. All three must produce
observable output. Never write code that silently swallows these:

1. Soft skips (invalid_payload, no_phone, below_threshold, already_sold):
   - Must store a skip_reason on the raw_record row. Not just skipped++.
   - Must be individually retrievable. "N rows skipped" is not enough.

2. Hard failures (thrown errors in processOneRow):
   - Must write processing_error to the raw_record row. (Already done.)
   - Must also emit a structured log entry with rawRecordId and error message.
   - finalizeFailure double-failures must not be swallowed. Re-throw or log.

3. Batch-level failures (RPC errors, claim failures):
   - Must emit a structured log entry before returning 500.
   - The log must include: timestamp, batch size attempted, error message.

Structured logging means: console.error(JSON.stringify({...})) at minimum today.
When Sentry is added, these become Sentry.captureException() calls with context.
Never use console.log for errors. Only console.error with a JSON payload.

## API routes
- Every route in app/api/ must be wrapped in withMonitoring().
- withMonitoring() is in lib/api.ts. Use it. Do not inline its logic.
- Every route must declare a flow tag:
  lead-capture | processing | qualification | handoff | admin | preview
- A catch block that only calls console.log, or is empty, is a build error.

## Supabase
- supabase db push --linked --include-all. Never push individual migrations.
- No seed data in migration files. Seed data in supabase/seed.sql.
- Always set Cache-Control: no-store on Supabase clients.
- Generated types in lib/database.types.ts. Run db:gen-types after every migration.
- RLS: no anon access. Service role on the server only.

## Validation
- Zod for all external input. No exceptions.
- Zod schemas live in lib/validation/. One file per vertical/context.
- A Zod parse failure is not a success. Do not call finalizeSuccess on parse failure.
  (This is a known bug in the current codebase. Fix it when you touch that path.)

## Testing
- Every new lib/ function gets a unit test in the same commit.
- Every new API route gets an integration test in the same commit.
- npm test must pass before every commit.
- Tests are reported pass/fail only. No console noise in test output.

## TypeScript
- No `any` without a comment explaining why it cannot be avoided.
- Strict mode is on. Do not work around it.

## Documentation
- New migration → update schema section of docs/STATE.md.
- New env var → add to docs/env-vars.md and .env.example.
- Non-obvious decision → create ADR in docs/adr/.
- Do not update docs that did not change.

## AI assistant behavior
- Read before editing. Explore relevant files first.
- Edit minimally. Change only what the task requires.
- Do not refactor code you were not asked to refactor.
- Do not rename things without being asked.
- Exception: if you encounter a silent catch block or a finalizeSuccess-on-parse-failure
  while working on adjacent code, flag it as a finding. Do not fix it silently.
- When adding an API route: add withMonitoring() automatically.
- When adding a lib/ function: add its test automatically.
- Before any DB command: state what it will do and wait for confirmation.
- Never push to prod without explicit instruction.
- Never use country names in generated code, types, or copy.
